# ─── Krites environment ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to .env and fill in. NEVER commit .env. Krites also reads these straight
# from the process environment, which is the recommended path for CI.
# Precedence everywhere: a real process env var ALWAYS wins over a value in .env.

# Claude — powers the read-only reviewer (Claude Agent SDK). Provide ONE of:
#   1. CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN — a Claude Code token from `claude setup-token`
#      (uses your Claude Pro/Max subscription; preferred, especially for CI), or
#   2. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — a metered Anthropic API key, or
#   3. nothing here + an existing `claude login` session (SDK auto-discovers it locally).
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# GitHub — Krites's OWN identity (never Boule's or Praktor's). An auto-merger has
# merge rights, so it is a higher-privilege identity and gets its own GitHub App.
# Auth resolves in this order: the KRITES_APP_* trio (preferred) → a PAT fallback.
#
#   GitHub App (preferred for autonomous CI bots). Required App permissions:
#     Contents: read/write, Pull requests: read/write, Issues: read/write,
#     Discussions: read/write, Checks: read, Metadata: read.
#   Do NOT grant Administration — Krites must not be able to edit its own branch
#   protection or CI. Branch protection is the real merge gate; Krites is layer two.
# KRITES_APP_ID=
# KRITES_APP_INSTALLATION_ID=
# Private key accepts a raw PEM, a file path, or a single-line base64 blob:
#   base64 -w0 your-app.private-key.pem   (macOS: base64 -i your-app.private-key.pem)
# NOTE for CI: when feeding this to actions/create-github-app-token, store it as a
# RAW PEM and pass the secret DIRECTLY — never decode it in a run step (a derived
# value is not masked and gets echoed into logs).
# KRITES_APP_PRIVATE_KEY=

#   PAT fallback (simpler, less preferred). The built-in Actions GITHUB_TOKEN
#   cannot enable auto-merge across protected branches, so use a fine-grained PAT.
# KRITES_GITHUB_TOKEN=
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Target repository & project (can also be passed via --repo/--project).
# KRITES_REPO falls back to GITHUB_REPOSITORY when unset (set automatically in Actions).
# KRITES_REPO=owner/repo
# KRITES_PROJECT=1

# Behaviour knobs (all have safe defaults validated by the zod config schema):
# KRITES_TRUSTED_AUTHOR=praktorai[bot]   # only auto-merge PRs from this login (Praktor's bot)
# KRITES_MERGE_METHOD=squash             # squash | merge | rebase
# KRITES_REQUIRE_CI=true                 # refuse to enable merge unless checks are green
# KRITES_MAX_MERGES=1                    # blast-radius cap: max auto-merges enabled per run
# KRITES_LOG_LEVEL=info
